Description.LocalizedString: The Observer’s model of a universe devoid of auric energy.
A model of a universe birthing auric energy.
A model depicting a vibrant universe bursting with the chaos of life, death, and the existence in between.
A model of a universe consuming itself. Oddly beautiful.
A celebration to the success of No Spin after the addition of Ji-Woon Hak.
Usually reserved for K-pop artists, Yun-Jin held a special celebrity status that was cause for her own lightstick.
A limited-edition gamepad featuring Feng Min’s esports team, the Laser Bears.
Sometimes in business you’ve got to put your foot down and get tough.
Feng Min’s avatar, owing to her nickname, “The Shining Lion.”
When you hit the big times, you fly in style.
Memorabilia for a musical group from South Korea. Four of five members died in a studio fire.
Music so mesmerizing you can see it.
An officially licensed pair of earbuds. Same product, extra cost.
Herman Carter enjoyed a good game of chess, and the power he felt after weakening an opponent.
A ticket to The Trickster’s concert stop in Brazil.
Decapitated, gutted, and stabbed. An altogether bad day for this bird.
The logo of one South Korea’s top record labels. It has direct ties to Yun-Jin Lee and Ji-Woon Hak.
A photocard of Ji-Woon Hak, it became a popular collectible among his fans.
The Doctor’s experiments usually ended with flat lines.
A tool used by Yun-Jin and The Trickster when producing music.
The logo of Feng Min’s esports team. While representing the Laser Bears, she became the Nebula Arc champion.
The desire to create agonizing art surfaced again, and a victim had been chosen...
He cried tears for his deceased bandmates, but inside he was laughing hysterically.
The game was far from over, and he’d do anything to keep from being caught.
He set his victim free and took a punch to the face. This would be his best trick yet.
He played himself off as the victim. He couldn’t let them find out.
She had bigger dreams and it would require some strategic moves to reach them.
Dealing with The Trickster was becoming much more than a full-time job.
She found signs that The Trickster’s darkness ran deeper than she thought.
She’d keep the pedal to the floor, literally, if it meant figuring out what The Trickster was up to.
The seed of doubt had been planted. Every time she looked at The Trickster, an alarm in her head went off.
Useful for when The Doctor kept a subject alive to prolong the torture.
Who’s the spooky ghost under the sheet?
A streetwise effigy that keeps the crows away.
A cat with a smart fashion sense.

In the end, we’re nothing but captive hearts.

Design inspired by Cozaco.

An unusual gaming device from another dimension. Remember to feed your Entity!

Design inspired by Chessa.
An unusual shape found in The Entity’s realm. It often leads to terror.
A relic from a faraway place, where factions battle for survival.
A rare kabuki mask that only materializes in a small number of dimensions.
An unusual design that may mean something to those in another universe.
